From: ESP32-S3 Web Simulator contributors
Subject: [PATCH] m25p80: support GigaDevice status register 2 QE bit

ESP-IDF 4.4 initializes the 8 MiB GigaDevice flash selected by the ESP32-S3
machine by reading status register 2 with 0x35, writing its QE bit with 0x31,
and reading it back. The model only implemented those status-register-2 paths
for Winbond, so the write payload was decoded as a new command and default
flash initialization failed.

GigaDevice uses the same status-register-2 QE bit position for this path. Apply
the existing Winbond behavior to GigaDevice parts as well.

SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-only
---
 hw/block/m25p80.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/hw/block/m25p80.c b/hw/block/m25p80.c
--- a/hw/block/m25p80.c
+++ b/hw/block/m25p80.c
@@ -834,6 +834,7 @@ static void complete_collecting_data(Flash *s)
         break;
     case WRSR2:
         switch (get_man(s)) {
+        case MAN_GIGADEVICE:
         case MAN_WINBOND:
             s->quad_enable = !!(s->data[0] & 0x02);
             break;
@@ -1322,4 +1323,5 @@ static void decode_new_cmd(Flash *s, uint32_t value)
         switch (get_man(s)) {
+        case MAN_GIGADEVICE:
         case MAN_WINBOND:
             s->needed_bytes = 1;
             s->state = STATE_COLLECTING_DATA;
@@ -1499,6 +1501,7 @@ static void decode_new_cmd(Flash *s, uint32_t value)
         case MAN_MACRONIX:
             s->quad_enable = true;
             break;
+        case MAN_GIGADEVICE:
         case MAN_WINBOND:
             s->data[0] = (!!s->quad_enable) << 1;
             s->pos = 0;
